[FEAT] Advanced Sleep, Petal Decor, New Advancements & More (v1.1.1)
This update introduces the "Path to Slumber" advanced sleep system, new hamster decoration mechanics, additional advancements, and numerous QoL improvements and bug fixes.
**Features & Additions:**
- **Advanced Sleep System for Tamed Hamsters:** - Implemented a multi-stage "Path to Slumber" for tamed, sitting hamsters, controlled by a new `DozingPhase` enum and associated timers (`quiescentSitDurationTimer`, `driftingOffTimer`, `settleSleepAnimationCooldown`). - New animations: `anim_hamster_drifting_off`, `anim_hamster_settle_sleep1`, `anim_hamster_settle_sleep2`, `anim_hamster_settle_sleep3`, and looping poses `anim_hamster_sleep_pose1`, `anim_hamster_sleep_pose2`, `anim_hamster_sleep_pose3`. - Wild hamsters now use a triggerable `anim_hamster_wild_settle_sleep` before looping `anim_hamster_sleep_pose1`. - Player interactions (via `interactMob`) now correctly call `resetSleepSequence()` to interrupt dozing/sleeping states. - Sleep state persistence implemented via NBT (`DozingPhase`, timers, `currentDeepSleepAnimationId`). - **Configurable Sleep Mechanics:** Added to `ModConfigModel.HamsterBehaviorSettings` and `ModConfigModel.FeatureToggleSettings`: - `tamedQuiescentSitMinSeconds`, `tamedQuiescentSitMaxSeconds` - `tamedSleepThreatDetectionRadiusBlocks` - `requireDaytimeForTamedSleep` - **Pink Petal Decoration & Removal:** - Right-clicking with `Items.PINK_PETALS` on a tamed hamster now cycles its `PINK_PETAL_TYPE` DataTracker (0-3). - Right-clicking with `Items.SHEARS` removes petals (sets `PINK_PETAL_TYPE` to 0) and drops one `Items.PINK_PETALS`. - **New Advancements & Criteria:** - "Petal Pusher" (`petal_pusher.json`): Triggers on `ModCriteria.APPLIED_PINK_PETAL`. - "Pocket Paramedic" (`pocket_paramedic.json`): Triggers on `ModCriteria.HAMSTER_AUTO_FED`. - "Nose for Treasure" (`nose_for_treasure.json`): Triggers on `ModCriteria.HAMSTER_DIAMOND_ALERT_TRIGGERED`. - "Impending Doom Squeak" (`impending_doom_squeak.json`): Triggers on `ModCriteria.HAMSTER_CREEPER_ALERT_TRIGGERED`. - "Chipmunk Aspirations" (`chipmunk_aspirations.json`): Triggers on `ModCriteria.HAMSTER_POUCH_FILLED`. - **"Sweet Potato" Easter Egg:** Implemented via hidden advancement (`technical/sweet_potato_named.json`) and functions (`technical/check_sweet_potato_name.mcfunction`, `technical/sweet_potato_effects.mcfunction`) for one-time effects per player (using flag `technical/sweet_potato_easter_egg_triggered_flag.json`). Removed old Java-based check from `interactMob`. - **Behavioral Enhancements:** - Hamsters avoid water and fire/lava via `setPathfindingPenalty(PathNodeType.WATER, -1.0F)` etc. in constructor. - Added `ModSounds.HAMSTER_SHOULDER_MOUNT_SOUNDS` (randomized) and `ModSounds.HAMSTER_DISMOUNT`.
**Changes & Improvements:**
- **Auto-Eat Mechanics:** - Introduced `preAutoEatDelayTicks` (2s) before `isAutoEating` state in `HamsterEntity.tick()`. - Increased `autoEatCooldownTicks` to 60 ticks. - **Visuals & Audio:** - Melee attack particles changed from `ParticleTypes.POOF` to `ParticleTypes.CRIT` (10 count, 0.2 Y-spread, 0.05 speed) in `AdorableHamsterPets.handleSpawnAttackParticlesPacket`. - Updated hamster eye textures. - `ModSounds.CHEESE_USE_SOUND` now plays at hamster's last pos; mount sounds play at player's pos. - **Configuration (`ModConfigModel.java`):** - Restructured with more descriptive top-level classes (e.g., `HamsterBehaviorSettings`, `FeatureToggleSettings`) and internal `@SectionHeader`s. - Settings relocated (e.g., sleep timers to `HamsterBehaviorSettings`). - Updated `en_us.json` to reflect new config structure and keys. - **Animation Control:** - `HamsterEntity.registerControllers()` updated for new sleep animation states (`DRIFTING_OFF_ANIM`, `SLEEP_POSE1/2/3_ANIM`) and triggerable settle anims (`SETTLE_SLEEP1/2/3_ANIM`, `WILD_SETTLE_SLEEP_ANIM`). - `HamsterModel.setCustomAnimations()` updated to manage `closed_eyes` bone visibility during sleep, KO, and `wakingUpTicks` states, allowing animations to control eye appearance.
**Fixes:**
- **Animation Sync:** Resolved "sliding sit bug" by overriding `HamsterEntity.setInSittingPose` to synchronize vanilla sitting pose with the custom `IS_SITTING` DataTracker. - **Rotation Lock:** Implemented `HamsterLookAtEntityGoal` and `HamsterLookAroundGoal` to prevent head/body rotation when `isSitting()`, `isSleeping()`, or `isKnockedOut()`. - **Targeting Logic:** - Refined `HamsterEntity.canAttackWithOwner` to correctly exclude other player-owned `AnimalEntity` / `Ownable` pets (including `AbstractHorseEntity`). - Overrode `HamsterEntity.setTarget` to prevent retaliation against owner's other pets. - **Ambient Sounds:** Corrected `HamsterEntity.getAmbientSound()` to play sleep sounds only during actual sleep phases and ensure silence when `isKnockedOut()`.

[FEAT] Implement Ore Seeking, Animation Personalities, and Config Overhaul
This major feature release introduces the independent ore-seeking behavior for hamsters, adds unique animation personalities, and migrates from owo-lib to Fzzy Config. It also includes a significant overhaul of the footstep sound system and numerous bug fixes.
- [FEAT] Added Independent Ore Seeking behavior. - Hamsters primed by a shoulder diamond alert can now seek out diamond ore upon dismount. - Includes a chance to "mistakenly" find gold, resulting in a new "sulking" state. - Implemented new AI goal (`HamsterSeekDiamondGoal`) and associated animations (`seeking`, `wants_to_seek`, `sulk`), sounds, and particle effects. - Added "Canine Aspirations?" advancement for successfully finding diamonds.
- [FEAT] Added Animation Personalities. - Hamsters are now assigned a persistent personality ID (1-3) on spawn. - This ID determines which of the three new sitting and dozing animations the hamster will use for its entire life. - State is saved to NBT and shoulder data.
- [FEAT] Added Jade integration for block tooltips and an advanced, configurable hamster debug overlay.
- [FEAT] Added a new looping sound effect for the cleaning animation.
- [FEAT] Added configurable cleaning frequency via Fzzy Config.
- [REFACTOR] Migrated from owo-lib to Fzzy Config for all configuration management.
- [REFACTOR] Overhauled the footstep sound system to a hybrid model. - Client-side, animation-synced keyframes are used when the entity is rendered. - Server-side, movement-based sounds are used as a fallback when the entity is off-screen. - Implemented a client-side render-tracking system with a new attachment (`HamsterRenderState`) and network payload (`UpdateHamsterRenderStatePayload`).
- [REFACTOR] Replaced procedural blinking logic with animation keyframes for better control.
- [STYLE] Adjusted volume for begging and gravel footstep sounds for better balance.
- [FIX] Corrected biome variant spawning logic to properly handle Stony Shores, Windswept biomes, Jungles, Deep Dark, and Old Growth Birch Forests.
- [FIX] Resolved an issue where the `maxGroupSize` config value was not being accessed correctly. This was actually a confirmed bug in owo-lib, but since the mod now uses Fzzy Config, this issue is no longer present.
- [FIX] Fixed a bug where wild hamsters would incorrectly load in a sitting state.
- [FIX] Corrected the crafting and NBT application logic for the Hamster Guide Book to be more robust.
- [FIX] Refined AI goals (`HamsterFollowOwnerGoal`, `HamsterLookAtEntityGoal`, `HamsterLookAroundGoal`) to prevent unwanted movement or rotation during new states like sulking and celebrating.
- [DOC] Updated `README.md` with instructions for the new Jade debug overlay and a section for the new animation personalities feature.
- [DOC] Updated `fabric.mod.json` to correctly declare dependencies and suggestions.
- [CHORE] Updated project license to a split model (MIT for code, All Rights Reserved for assets) and renamed LICENSE file to LICENSE.md.

[FIX] Prevent crash on world exit by adding network guard clause
The client was attempting to send hamster render state packets every tick, even after disconnecting from a world. This caused an `IllegalStateException` because the network handler was no longer available.
This commit fixes the issue by adding a guard clause to the client tick handler, ensuring that network packets are only sent when `client.world` and `client.player` are not null. The tick event listeners have also been consolidated for better code clarity.

[FIX] Prevent crash on world exit by adding network guard clause
The client was attempting to send hamster render state packets every tick, even after disconnecting from a world. This caused an `IllegalStateException` because the network handler was no longer available.
This commit fixes the issue by adding a guard clause to the client tick handler, ensuring that network packets are only sent when `client.world` and `client.player` are not null. The tick event listeners have also been consolidated for better code clarity.
